      <head>Marie Schneider-Grünzweig</head>
      <div>
        <p>Austrian social activist in music.</p>
        <p>Schneider-Grünzweig was a pianist until an arm accident prevented her from pursuing
          a professional career on that instrument. From 1893 to 1928, she was President and
          single-handed organizer of the professional body, the <ref cRef="entity-002438">Verein der Musiklehrerinnen</ref> in Vienna. In 1896 she started the Association's
          pension fund, but this was lost in the currency devaluation after 1918.</p>
        <p>When the <ref cRef="musikpadagogenverban">Österreichischer
            Musikpädagogenverband</ref> was founded in 1911, she was the sole female member of
          its founding committee.</p>
        <p>There is no known correspondence between Schneider-Grünzweig and Schenker.</p>
      </div>
